						<summary>

						<p>Ceiling of the <hi rend="italic">Kalyāṇa-maṇḍapa</hi> on the compound of the Agastyeśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1692 (current), Khara, Jyēshṭa ba. 10,</hi> corresponding to 1771 A.D., June 8, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a <hi rend="italic">Kalyāṇa-maṇṭapa</hi> to god Agastiśvara by Śiṁgari, son of Peda-Gōpālayya, the Karṇam of Pālūru.</p>						

